sp;&nbsp;2600&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Carlsbad State Beach&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;4200&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Carlsbad Premium Outlets&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;6000&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Fletcher Cove&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;1100&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Solana Beach Towne Center&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;3600&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Oceanside Pier&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;3300&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Military Bases — 111,600</summary>\n\n<table style=\"width: auto\">\n<tr><th align=\"left\">Name</th><th align=\"right\">Modeled Demand</th></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Marine Corps Air Station Miramar&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;7400&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Marine Corps Recruit Depot San Diego&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;3600&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Naval Amphibious Base Coronado&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;3200&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Naval Air Station North Island&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;23,400&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Naval Base Point Loma&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;6600&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Naval Base San Diego&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;23,400&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align=\"right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;44,000&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n</details>\n<br>\n\n<h2>Additional Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Building Collision</strong> — A buildings index is included, providing in-game collision geometry for all non-filtered buildings.</li>\n<li><strong>Neighborhood Labels</strong> — The map includes municipal and neighborhood labels derived from administrative boundary data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Methodology</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>MX data:<ul>\n<li>Processed INEGI&#39;s DENUE, CE, and CPV data sets for the entire country.</li>\n<li>Estimated business job counts by taking the geometric means of strata.</li>\n<li>Aggregated businesses to the block level.</li>\n<li>Estimated uncounted/informal jobs via the ENOE data set.</li>\n<li>Extracted relevant points for the bounding box of this map, then applied a modified version of Colin&#39;s gravity model.</li>\n<li>Added special demand via the Demand Adder.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>US data:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rslurry/subwaybuilder-US-demand-data\">subwaybuilder-US-demand-generator</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Border data:<ul>\n<li>Assumes 50% of crossing happen from US side, and 50% happen from MX side. Values rounded down to ensure an equal number of pops for both.  Commutes to/from the border point are separately done for MX and US sub-maps (where pops live/work at the border crossing and work/live somewhere in the city), then pops are paired up to form commutes from MX to US and vice versa.  A 30 minute border crossing time penalty is applied to the commute.  The Cross Border Xpress is exempt for this model, since it exists as a way for pops to enter/exit TIJ airport on the US side, and so the border crossing time does not impact the commute to/from CBX, and these pops do not have any origin/destination in MX.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Data Sources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.inegi.org.mx/programas/ce/2024/\">INEGI Censos Económicos (CE) 2024</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.inegi.org.mx/app/mapa/denue/default.aspx\">INEGI Directorio Estadístico Nacional de Unidades Económicas (DENUE)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.inegi.org.mx/programas/ccpv/2020/\">INEGI Censo de Población y Vivienda (CPV) 2020</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.inegi.org.mx/programas/enoe/15ymas/\">INEGI Encuesta Nacional de Ocupación y Empleo (ENOE)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lehd.ces.census.gov/data/\">US Census Bureau LEHD Origin-Destination Employment Statistics (LODES)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://data.bts.gov/stories/s/jswi-2e7b\">US Bureau of Transportation Statistics Border Crossing/Entry Data</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>License</h2>\n<p>This map data is released under the <a href=\"https://github.com/rslurry/subwaybuilder-maps/blob/main/LICENSE\">GNU General Public License v3.0</a>.</p>\n<h2>Credits</h2>\n<p>Map authored by slurry</p>",
